### Authenticate User via GraphQL Login Mutation

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/authentication/operations.mdx

This GraphQL mutation demonstrates how to log in a user by providing their email and password. A successful mutation returns the authenticated user's details, token, and its expiration, and automatically sets an HTTP-only cookie.

```graphql
mutation {
  login[collection-singular-label](email: "dev@payloadcms.com", password: "yikes") {
    user {
      email
    }
    exp
    token
  }
}
```

