### POST /api/[collection-slug]/login

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/authentication/operations.mdx

This endpoint allows a user to log in by providing their email and password. Upon successful authentication, it returns the logged-in user's details and an authentication token. In REST and GraphQL APIs, it also sets an HTTP-only cookie with the user's token.

```APIDOC
## POST /api/{collection-slug}/login

### Description
This endpoint allows a user to log in by providing their email and password. Upon successful authentication, it returns the logged-in user's details and an authentication token. In REST and GraphQL APIs, it also sets an HTTP-only cookie with the user's token.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/api/{collection-slug}/login

### Parameters
#### Path Parameters
- **collection-slug** (string) - Required - The slug of the collection that the user belongs to.

#### Query Parameters
*None*

#### Request Body
- **email** (string) - Required - The email address of the user attempting to log in.
- **password** (string) - Required - The password of the user attempting to log in.

### Request Example
{
  "email": "dev@payloadcms.com",
  "password": "this-is-not-our-password...or-is-it?"
}

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **user** (object) - The logged-in user's details.
- **user.email** (string) - The email address of the logged-in user.
- **user.createdAt** (string) - ISO 8601 timestamp of when the user account was created.
- **user.updatedAt** (string) - ISO 8601 timestamp of when the user account was last updated.
- **user.id** (string) - The unique identifier of the user.
- **token** (string) - The authentication token for the logged-in user.
- **exp** (number) - Unix timestamp indicating when the user's token will expire.

#### Response Example
{
  "user": {
    "email": "dev@payloadcms.com",
    "createdAt": "2020-12-27T21:16:45.645Z",
    "updatedAt": "2021-01-02T18:37:41.588Z",
    "id": "5ae8f9bde69e394e717c8832"
  },
  "token": "34o4345324...",
  "exp": 1609619861
}
```

