### Authenticate User and Obtain JWT Token in Payload

Source: https://context7.com/payloadcms/payload/llms.txt

Verify user credentials using email and password to obtain a JWT token for authenticated requests. The example shows login procedures, token usage in request headers, and verifying authentication from incoming requests with permission checks.

```typescript
import { getPayload } from 'payload'
import config from '@/payload.config'

const payload = await getPayload({ config })

// Login with email/password
const result = await payload.login({
  collection: 'users',
  data: {
    email: 'user@example.com',
    password: 'securePassword123',
  },
})

console.log(`Token: ${result.token}`)
console.log(`User: ${result.user.email}, Role: ${result.user.role}`)

// Use token in subsequent requests
const headers = {
  'Authorization': `Bearer ${result.token}`,
}

// Verify authentication from request
const authResult = await payload.auth({
  headers: request.headers,
})

if (authResult.user) {
  console.log(`Authenticated as ${authResult.user.email}`)
  console.log(`Permissions:`, authResult.permissions)
}
```

