Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/examples/auth/README.md

Demonstrates how to authenticate users server-side using Payload's Local API within a Next.js application. It fetches user permissions and details, redirecting to login if the user is not authenticated. It relies on the 'payload' package and the Next.js 'headers' module.

```typescript
import { headers as getHeaders } from 'next/headers.js'
import { getPayload } from 'payload'
import config from '../../payload.config'

export default async function AccountPage({ searchParams }) {
  const headers = await getHeaders()
  const payload = await getPayload({ config: configPromise })
  const { permissions, user } = await payload.auth({ headers })

  if (!user) {
    redirect(
      `/login?error=${encodeURIComponent('You must be logged in to access your account.')}&redirect=/account`,
    )
  }

  return ...

```

