### Perform authentication operation in Payload CMS (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/local-api/overview.mdx

This snippet shows how to perform an authentication operation using Payload CMS's local API. It requires `headers` (potentially from `next/headers` for Next.js environments) and can be configured to set response headers. The result includes user `permissions`, the authenticated `user` document, and `responseHeaders`.

